{{US-med-bio-stub}}

[[image:SaltLakeNight.jpg|thumb|The northern section of the cemetery at night, looking towards Salt Lake City]]

The [[Salt Lake City Cemetery]] is in [[The Avenues, Salt Lake City, Utah|The Avenues]] neighborhood of [[Salt Lake City, Utah]].  Approximately 120,000 persons are buried in the cemetery.  Many religious leaders and politicians, particularly many leaders of [[The Church of Jesus Christ of Latter-day Saints]] (LDS Church) lie in the cemetery.  It encompasses over {{convert|250|acre|km2}} and contains 9{{frac|1|2}} miles of roads.  It is the largest city-operated cemetery in the [[United States]].

